ByArman Shirinyan





On Tuesday, Vetle Lunde of K33 Research noted that the amount of Bitcoin managed by global exchange-traded products (ETPs) has now reached a new peak for the first time since January.

After solid flows yesterday, the bitcoin under management by global ETPs is back where it belongs, at all-time highs.Net inflows since April 10: 81,466 BTC. pic.twitter.com/XkfxiV8GB3

