Roland Garros qualifying action continued with second-round action Wednesday, with players trying to earn their way into the main draw of the clay-court major.

Before rain interrupted play, second seed Alexander Shevchenko held off France's Mathys Erhard for a 3-6, 6-3, 7-6(5) victory, winning the final eight points from 2/5 in the decisive tie-break against the home favourite. The Kazakhstani saved six of 12 break points, according to Infosys Stats, to move within one victory of his third consecutive Roland Garros main-draw appearance.

Tenth seed Elmer Moller, 11th seed Ethan Quinn, 16th seed Tristan Boyer and 24th seed Thiago Agustin Tirante also advanced before the rain came in Paris.

