TUCSON, Ariz. (13 News) - 13 News has received several calls, messages, and texts about a mysterious object floating in the Tucson sky over the last few days.

Turns out it isn't a space jellyfish, spy balloon, or UFO.

According to Flight Radar and FAA records, it is a stratospheric, high-altitude balloon from South Dakota-based aerospace company Aerostar.

As of 4 p.m. Tuesday, the balloon was around 62,000 feet. One caller said you could get a good view of it in the Foothills area, especially near Swan and River.

