Bitcoin BTC$106,546.31 clinched a fresh record price of $109,400, surpassing the peak in January around Donald Trump's inauguration.According to the CoinDesk Bitcoin Index, the largest and oldest cryptocurrency hit $109,486 on Wednesday during the early U.S. session. BTC surged more than 46% from its April trough induced by mounting freas over global trade war and U.S. tariffs.

