g AMP-PNP (cyan sticks) bound SLC35B1 structure (orange, teal and grey) with the occluded CMP-Sialic acid SLC35A1 (structure PDB: 6OH2, transparent pink). right: As in the left panel as viewed from the side. If the cytoplasmic-facing SLC35B1 protein would adopt a similar occluded conformation as SLC35A1, then the inward movement of TM8-TM9 gating helices (white arrow) would physically clash with the bound nucleotide.

