Unseeded in Strasbourg, she battled past in-form fellow American Sofia Kenin in the first round to book an intriguing clash against a resurgent Raducanu, who enjoyed a fourth-round run of her own at the Foro Italico just last week.Raducanu opened her Strasbourg campaign with an impressive upset over No. 6 seed Daria Kasatkina, and edged through the opening set over Collins before finding herself on the back for in the second, later calling for an injury timeout.Collins looked to consolidate a break advantage early in the decider but Raducanu kept battling, leveling the set at three games apiece. Collins stepped in to break right back and spent the ensuing changeover standing up for herself and Raducanu, imploring a encroaching cameraman to step back as they attempted to rehydrate.“We're on a changeover,” she told the cameraman, who was stationed between the two players. “You don't need to be that close to me and you don't need to be on top of Emma. It's wildly inappropriate.”Spurred on by the incident, Collins roared through the match's conclusion, breaking once more to clinch the win in just under two and a half hours.

