"https://news.google.com/rss/search?q=site:pitchfork.com","Girlpool's Avery Tucker Shares Video for Debut Solo Single: Watch","https://pitchfork.com/news/girlpool-avery-tucker-shares-video-for-debut-solo-single-watch/","Wed, 21 May 2025 14:04:28 GMT","

Avery Tucker, formerly half of Girlpool, has shared a new song. “Big Drops” is Tucker's debut solo single, and he co-wrote and co-produced it with frequent A. G. Cook collaborator Alaska Reid. In a press statement, he described the song as “a story about loving and losing someone who is finding themselves time and time again overtaken by the big drop.” Watch the accompanying music video, directed by Lilliya Scarlett Reid, below.

Girlpool, the Los Angeles–based duo of Tucker and Harmony Tividad, broke up in 2022, a few months after the release of their final album, Forgiveness. Last year, Tividad shared the album Gossip, her first proper studio album.

